articles.title: US returns Egon Schiele art stolen by Nazis to heirs - BBC
articles.description: Jewish performer Fritz Grünbaum, who owned the Egon Schiele pieces, was killed by the Nazis in 1941.
articles.content:
The US has returned seven artworks by Austrian painter Egon Schiele to the heirs of a Jewish cabaret star who owned them before he was killed by the Nazis in 1941.
